&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Motive is a dynamic agency and creative collective operating at the speed of culture. We’re a collective of deep thinkers, creative makers, cultural connoisseurs, and executional aces. We create meaningful engagements between brands and their audiences, cultivating relationships that drive tangible results for our clients. And we do it with sharp strategy and powerful creative executed across all the media and touch-points key to our targets’ lives.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;As pioneers in the area of content, digital engagement, and innovative experiential programs, and award winners for work in TV, event, digital and social, Motive has created a culture where every individual is given an opportunity to stretch and flex their creative and executional muscles daily. We are a team of hard-working, fast-moving, energetic, passionate, driven, straight-talking creative thinkers. We like being challenged and we love the collaboration necessary to overcome the challenges and succeed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;If this sounds like a place you would thrive, let’s see if we can make something happen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ACCOUNT COORDINATOR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;At Motive, our Account Coordinators are the engine that keeps great work moving. As an Account Coordinator, you&#39;ll support the day-to-day management of key client relationships while helping ensure projects move seamlessly from kickoff through delivery. Working alongside Account leaders, Strategists, Creatives, Producers, and cross-functional teams, you&#39;ll help bring integrated marketing programs to life across traditional, experiential, digital, social, retail, commerce and content channels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;This role is ideal for someone who is highly organized, proactive, curious, and excited to build a career in agency account management. You&#39;ll develop a deep understanding of our clients&#39; businesses while learning how exceptional client service and operational excellence create impactful work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the day-to-day management of a key client account, ensuring projects are organized, on schedule, and delivered with excellence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate project timelines, deliverables, meeting agendas, status updates, and follow-up actions across internal teams and clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in developing clear project briefs and ensuring work aligns with client objectives and strategic direction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with creative, strategy, production, media, and project management teams throughout the lifecycle of assignments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help manage multiple integrated projects simultaneously, keeping teams informed of priorities, timelines, and next steps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor project progress, identify potential challenges early, and help facilitate solutions to keep work moving forward.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build strong working relationships with clients through responsive communication, professionalism, and attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop an understanding of client&#39;s business, industry, competitive landscape, and brand objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in internal brainstorms, planning sessions, client meetings, presentations, and agency initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support project financial administration, including estimates, purchase orders, invoices, and budget tracking, as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
