&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;● Support and Reporting: Partner with the Market Manager to execute retail strategies and&amp;nbsp;provide comprehensive reports on field activities and performance metrics&lt;br&gt;● Retail Communication and Relations: Cultivate and sustain strong relationships with&amp;nbsp;retail partners to ensure smooth program operations, addressing and resolving issues&amp;nbsp;with professionalism.&lt;br&gt;● Leadership and Development: Guide and develop Field Specialists by providing&amp;nbsp;essential tools and knowledge. Assisting with regular training sessions and ongoing&amp;nbsp;support.&lt;br&gt;● Program Optimization: Collect and analyze on-site feedback to refine program tactics,&amp;nbsp;while implementing effective solutions to boost program efficiency.&lt;br&gt;● Inventory Oversight: Aide in distribution and tracking of program materials and assets,&amp;nbsp;ensuring timely communication of issues and escalation as needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;● 1-3 years of experience in field marketing, brand activation, retail engagement, or similar&amp;nbsp;roles.&lt;br&gt;● Proven supervisory experience with a strong focus on team development and coaching.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;● Solid understanding of compliance requirements in regulated industries and the ability to enforce guidelines consistently.&lt;br&gt;● Highly organized with excellent problem-solving skills and meticulous attention to detail.&lt;br&gt;● Demonstrated ability to quickly learn and articulate detailed product information.&lt;br&gt;● Strong communication skills with a talent for building meaningful relationships.&lt;br&gt;● Availability to work a flexible schedule, including evenings and weekends as needed.&lt;br&gt;● Must be 25+ years of age with a valid driver&#39;s license and reliable transportation.&lt;br&gt;● In-market travel required up to a 40-mile radius.&lt;/p&gt;
