&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are seeking a highly motivated Market Manager to serve as the market point of contact for a&amp;nbsp;multi-week retail engagement program in a highly regulated industry (tobacco/nicotine). The&amp;nbsp;ideal candidate thrives in dynamic environments, leads market teams with confidence, and has&amp;nbsp;a proven ability to engage store managers and consumers while ensuring program compliance&amp;nbsp;and accuracy. This role requires equal parts people leadership, operational oversight, and on-the-ground presence to deliver results at the highest standard.&amp;nbsp;The Market Manager will oversee all in-market execution, ensuring store readiness, inventory management, and accurate field audits and recaps. They will lead training, coaching, and talent development for a team of brand specialists, fostering performance excellence across teams.&amp;nbsp;The Market Manager is also responsible for elevating concerns, monitoring competitive activity,&amp;nbsp;and sharing best practices to drive continuous program optimization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;● Program Leadership: Manage and motivate a team of field specialists across a multi-week engagement program, ensuring they are trained, supported, and consistently&amp;nbsp;adhering to the retail engagement schedule and meeting performance standards&lt;br&gt;● Compliance &amp;amp; Accuracy: Uphold program integrity by monitoring adherence to regulatory&amp;nbsp;requirements, reviewing reports daily for accuracy and completeness, and correcting&amp;nbsp;discrepancies swiftly.&lt;br&gt;● Team Training &amp;amp; Development: Assist with onboarding and ongoing coaching of&amp;nbsp;specialists, ensuring they are equipped to confidently engage consumers and represent&amp;nbsp;the brand in a professional, compliant manner.&lt;br&gt;● Operational Excellence: Maintain accurate inventory of program materials and assets,&amp;nbsp;ensuring timely distribution, tracking, and accountability.&lt;br&gt;● Retail Engagement: Build and maintain strong relationships with retail partners through&amp;nbsp;weekly in-person visits and regular communications focused on activation scheduling,&amp;nbsp;inventory planning, consumer engagement, program feedback, and sales metrics.&lt;br&gt;● Reporting &amp;amp; Insights: Deliver timely feedback and actionable insights to internal teams,&amp;nbsp;identifying opportunities to improve execution, consumer engagement, and retailer&amp;nbsp;satisfaction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
